                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;02/16/2004&nbsp;: 5:08:53 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Parsed data for Critical Affliction 2 follows:<br /><pre id="code"><font face="courier" size="2" id="code">
Spell                     Crits  Total Ticks
----------------------    -----  -----------
Blood of Thule              12       254
Dark Plague                 19       259
Embracing Darkness          15       344
Funeral Pyre of Kelador    106      1616
Horror                      62      1062
Pyrocruor                   30       380
Saryrn's Kiss               21       284
Zevfeer's Theft of Vitae     1        10

Total                      266      4209</font id="code"></pre id="code"><br />For a total of 6.3%.  There doesn't seem to be any statistically significant difference based on which DoT is active, not that I was expecting any.  This is all my damage over time spells since obtaining Critical Affliction 2 recently, with the exception of Splurt.  I counted the ticks using MS Excel, and the risk of mis-counts seemed too high for Splurt.  (A crit of the first few ticks could be confused with normal damage from a later tick.)<br /><br />If anyone cares to try this on their own with MS Excel, the following cell entries may make it easier for you.  To return the <b>name</b> of a DoT, from a logfile entry that's been pasted into cell A1:<br /><br />=MID(A1,SEARCH("from your",A1)+10, LEN(A1)-SEARCH("from your",A1)-10)<br /><br />To return the <b>damage</b> done on that tick:<br /><br />=VALUE((MID(A1,SEARCH("has taken",A1)+9,(SEARCH("damage",A1) - SEARCH("has taken",A1)-9))))<br /><br />Once you have those set up, just sort by DoT name and damage.  It's pretty easy to spot the critical ticks.<br /><br /><br /><br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
